OL,3,C'Serious concerns' for safety of
OL,4,Cchildren at young offender institution
OL,6,FAccording to the Ministry of Justice
OL,7,Fthe number of children in custody has
OL,8,Ffallen by over 70% in the last decade
OL,9,F` from over 2000 in 2012 to an average
OL,10,Fof around 440 children in custody at
OL,11,Fany one time during the year 2022 to
OL,12,F2023, a fall of 3% against the
OL,13,Fprevious year and the lowest number on
OL,14,Frecord.
OL,16,FThey said that it creates a challenge
OL,17,Fas those in custody have largely
OL,18,Fcommitted violent offences, and are
OL,19,Fsome of the most complex and
OL,20,Fvulnerable children in the justice
OL,21,Fsystem, who require extensive support.
